
[1]specification

   SPECIFICA'TION, n.

   1. The act of determining by a mark or limit; notation of limits. The
   specification of limitation of the question hinders the disputers from
   wandering away from the precise point of inquiry.

   2. The act of specifying; designation of particulars; particular
   mention; as the specification of a charge against a military or naval
   officer.

   3. Article or thing specified.
